column5: It's not everyday I can go fish open water in my neck of the woods on January 14th and catch some nice water walleyes !!!

Nice fish, congrats on a good day out. It's pretty common to fish here in the winter as we have open water all year. However, it's not always comfortable to be out there fishing. This past weekend we had 70 degrees though. We got out and did some drop shot fishing for crappie in 25-30' of water. We ended up catching about 40 fish with the largest two fish being 2# 4oz and 1#12oz. Those were as large of crappies as I've ever caught. We also caught a bunch of other nice ones with only a few little ones mixed in.
Nice catch walleyecheek. Off topic I sent you a PM a while back. Wondering if you got it. Thanks!
Where is your neck of the woods? andersaki
Northern Iowa is my neck of the woods. I meant to put this post under General, but hit the Canada by mistake ?
Anytime you can get out is a good thing.nice catch.
I'm jealous! Some of our lakes still aren't totally iced up yet. Can't put a boat on, and not safe to walk on my local Walleye/perch water.
